        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "usp_Update_UpdateSBMRMeters",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to manage meter records in the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "SBMR.SBMRMeter",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " table. It processes an XML input containing meter information, updates existing records, inserts new records, and deletes records that are no longer present in the input. This procedure is part of a system that tracks meter numbers and associated account numbers, for a utility or service provider."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Medium"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The procedure involves multiple operations: parsing XML, inserting new records, updating existing records, and deleting obsolete records. The complexity arises from handling XML data, ensuring data integrity, and performing multiple conditional operations."
        }
      ]
    },
